E. COLI?, HEMOLYTIC UREMIC SYNDROME - USA (CONNECTICUT)
*******************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
E. coli, hemolytic uremic syndrome - USA (Georgia) 980626234520
E. coli, hemolytic uremic syndrome - USA (Georgia)(04) 980820225549
Date: Sat, 07 Aug 1999 07:09:38 -0400
From: Lisa Hofmann <scout@catskill.net>
Source: News media

Regional papers report that ten children, including three with hemolytic
uremic syndrome, became ill after swimming in a small private lake in East
Haddam, Connecticut. _E. Coli_ is suspected, but not confirmed as yet.
--
Lisa Hofmann
e-mail: scout@catskill.net
[Outbreaks of _E. coli_ O157 infection have been associated with
recreational swimming. We would like to be informed when the etiology of
this outbreak is confirmed. - Mod.ES
